-- Polyester Sanayi Falls 1st Day in Four in Istanbul Trading
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-22T15:28:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/polyester-sanayi-falls-1st-time-in-four-days-in-istanbul-trading.html
Polyester Sanayi AS (SASA) , a Turkish
producer of polyester fibers, yarns and plastic bottles,
dropped, snapping three days of gains.  Trading was halted on the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  in the
morning session after the stock retreated 11 percent. The shares
traded down 2.2 percent at 1.35 liras by the close in Istanbul.  “The shares rose by 24 percent in the last three trading
days on news that the Ministry of Economy decided to continue
with anti-dumping measures for polyester fiber imports from
Indonesia and  South Korea ,” Istanbul-based brokerage BGC
Partners said in a note to clients after the market closed
yesterday.  There is no specific reason for the shares’
“extraordinary” movements that has not been disclosed to the
public, the company said in a statement to the exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
